post_text: Tomorrow night at 7 p.m. is the monthly Mokena School District 159 board meeting. We are currently in Phase 4 of the Restore Illinois plan, which limits attendance to no more than 50 individuals. In order to accommodate any individuals that would like to view the meeting we have set up a live streaming option. You may view the meeting at this link: https://stream.meet.google.com/stream/57e1600f-f586-41e8-a4d4-10d9b3672f96. In addition to the live streaming option, an overflow space will be available in the Mokena Elementary School cafeteria. Thank you.

shared_text:
Mokena Community Public Library District
June 9 at 11:00 AM ¬∑

Join our Children's Librarian, Ms. Emily for another virtual Story Time. Tuesday, June 9th we are celebrating National Donald Duck Day by reading a Disney book featuring Mickey and friends, and our guest of honor, Donald Duck.

The story we are reading is called "Gone Surfin'" from the Disney's 5 Minute Stories Starring Mickey. In this story, Mickey and friends enjoy a nice summer day at the beach and learn how to surf. This books continues with our summer beach theme Story Times this week.

post_text: Thank you, Mokena Library!
shared_text:
Mokena Community Public Library District
May 20 at 9:45 AM ¬∑

We just refilled the bin with an awesome new Children's craft this morning. The craft is a Popsicle stick foam kite with googly eyes and a smile. All of the pieces are self-stick and the whole craft can be completed without glue or any other materials. Some parental assistance in tying the strings to the top and bottom of the craft may be needed for little ones. We hope you enjoy it!

These crafts are located in a pink bin outside the library's main entrance door. Please take only ONE (1) craft per child. These are free crafts for the community, so please think of your fellow community members before taking.

Again, please remember to practice safe social distancing and try to touch only the crafts you are going to take. All crafts have been individually packaged for sanitary purposes. A picture of what the craft looks like is provided below.

If interested, we will have these crafts out for the public until Saturday morning or until we run out of packages. Thank you! üòä

post_text: Thank you, Mokena Community Public Library District!
shared_text:
Mokena Community Public Library District
April 9 at 1:13 PM ¬∑

Starting today and for the rest of the weekend until we run out of crafts, we will have a bin of Easter-themed children's crafts available by the Mokena Library's main entrance. It is located to the left of the door. Please follow the instructions on the bin and practice safe social distancing if someone is near the bin.

Everything inside the bin has been wiped down and sanitized. Each craft is individually packaged as well. We recommend that you quickly grab which crafts you want from the bin and then walk away. Try not to congregate near the crafts and touch only the ones you would like to take home with you.

As we continue to navigate the uncharted territory as a result of the COVID-19 National Emergency, we are in need of additional information from families to continue to be able to provide students with educational opportunities during the school closure. At this time, we are now anticipating that school will resume on April 8, 2020, however, in these uncertain times it is necessary to make contingency plans.

It is pertinent that we gather information regarding the availability of the Internet and technology devices for school work in the homes of our families. If you haven't done so already, please complete this survey if you DO NOT have internet and/or access to a technology device for your child(ren) capable of connecting to internet and accessing Google.

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSernN0tFT1NVptOJKBcwew3SyrgeAx6Chmcjsu-9lpdQTithA/viewform

post_text: Update from the library:
shared_text:
Mokena Community Public Library District
March 13 at 5:15 PM ¬∑

Public Service Announcement

In the interest of putting the safety of our community first, we have made the difficult decision to close to the public beginning Monday, March 16th and will remain closed until further notice. These safety measures are being taken out of an abundance of caution, not due to any known exposure.

Because the safety and health of our employees and patrons is our first priority, the Mokena Community Public Library District will continue to monitor information from the CDC and local health departments so we can respond as conditions change regarding COVID-19.

While the library will be closed to the public, we will be fully staffed and available through phone: 708-479-9663 or email: mcpldstaff@mokena.lib.il.us during our hours of operation. We have many remote and digital services including eBooks, research databases, streaming music, online magazines, and more.

post_text:
Last week, we were given a tour of MJHS to see where money raised by the Mokena Educational Foundation goes!

First stop, science to learn about Gizmos, online simulations that help power student inquiry and conceptual understanding. Gizmos also allows students to conduct virtual experiments.

MEF donated money that went towards the newly remodeled fitness center, complete with 30 Spivy bikes, rowers, and other functional fitness equipment. This room is unlike any junior high level fitness center!

Our last stop was the Resource Center to learn about the newly-implemented Rebecca Caudill Reading Program and see the flexible seating, which allows students and staff to re-configure the room to their needs.

If you're interested in learning more about MEF, their next meeting is Tuesday, March 10!

post_text: In Mrs. Leo's art class, 4th and 5th graders have been exploring color theory in fun and interesting ways. 4th graders created patterns on coffee filters using markers and sprayed their artwork with water. The colors blended into new colors and we used the color chart to determine why. 5th graders also tried some color mixing...using shaving cream!! They splattered acrylic paint onto a bed of shaving cream, used q-tips to swirl the patterns, and then pressed card stock into the foam. Finally, they wiped the foam off for the "big reveal". The results were interesting marbled patterns!

post_text: Over winter break, MIS had a fitting fail on a hand-washing sink in one of our lunch huts. This hot water leak was not detected for several days and caused most of the wax on our cafeteria floor to start to come off. The cafeteria received a stripping and waxing. We discovered that part of our gym floor was buckling. Our insurance company inspected the floor and advised that we should get a new gym floor and discontinue using this gym. MIS staff has met and we have a plan for PE classes and arrival/dismissal procedures. Our new gym has a tentative completion date of the end of March/beginning of April.
